{ LOCAL INDUSTRY AND TRANSPORT}
Our{transport}developed to serve the {local industries, coal}and particularly{steel.}The local transport is{road, rail and canal.}The {canal}was the{first to be built,}and is now under{reconstruction}by the {South Yorkshire Navigation }with funds from the{E.E.C.}Regional Development fund. Our principle industry is steel at{ALDWARKE.}
There are records of{iron working}on this site in{Roman Times,}but the site became important in the mid Nineteenth Century and has progressively grown to its present size of{69 acres.}As well as steel making{ALDWARKE}is a modern{ {ROLLING MILL}working continuous shifts, employing many people.
